cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.SY 

This paper discusses the Sybil attack, which is a security issue in distributed networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Other possible categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
